title: PINEAPPLE ZUCCHINI BREAD
directions: Grease and flour two 8 x 4 inch loaf pans.
In a bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, baking powder and walnuts. Set aside.
In a separate large bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla. Beat in sugar until mixture is thick.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and flour mixture with a spoon until well mixed. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Test for doneness with a toothpick. Let bread cool for 10 minutes then remove from pans.
